,"body":"When GitHub issues an HTTP 302 response, the jcabi library creates an exception rather than following the redirect link located in the `Location` response header.  A 302 response is being incorrectly interpreted as an error, when it is not.\r\n\r\nBelow is the relevant message in the stack trace; I've removed my organization and repo information.  This is a private, enterprise level repository.\r\n> Exception in thread \"main\" java.lang.AssertionError: HTTP response status is not equal to 200:\r\n302 Found [https://api.github.com/repos/_MyOrganization_/_MyRepository_/contents/config/?ref=master]\r\n> Location: https://api.github.com/repositories/82982095/contents/config\r\n\r\n\r\nHere's the relevant excerpt from the GitHub developer documentation:\r\nhttps://developer.github.com/v3/#http-redirects\r\n\r\n> API v3 uses HTTP redirection where appropriate. Clients should assume that any request may result in a redirection. Receiving an HTTP redirection is not an error and clients should follow that redirect. Redirect responses will have a `Location` header field which contains the URI of the resource to which the client should repeat the requests.","closed_by":{"login":"amihaiemil","id":6305156,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjYzMDUxNTY=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/6305156?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/amihaiemil","html_url":"https://github.com/amihaiemil","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/amihaiemil/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/amihaiemil/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/amihaiemil/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/amihaiemil/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/amihaiemil/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/amihaiemil/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/amihaiemil/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/amihaiemil/events{/privacy